jnxUserAAAMib.description: This module defines the objects pertaining to User authentication, authorization and accounting

JnxAuthenticateType.name: JnxAuthenticateType
JnxAuthenticateType.description: There several way to authenticate a user, these are the types: radius - authentication via a radius server. local - local authenticaiton. ldap - authentication via a LDAP server. securid- authentication via RSA's SecurID authentication server jsrc - authentication via jsrc

JnxAccountingType.name: JnxAccountingType
JnxAccountingType.description: There several choices for accounting, these are the types: radius - accounting via a radius server. local - local accounting. ldap - accounting via a LDAP server. securid- accounting via RSA's SecurID accounting server jsrc - accounting via jsrc

JnxAuthorizationType.name: JnxAuthorizationType
JnxAuthorizationType.description: There several choices for authorization, these are the types: radius - authorization via a radius server. local - local authorization. ldap - authorization via a LDAP server. securid- authorization via RSA's SecurID authorization server jsrc - authorization via jsrc

JnxProvisioningType.name: JnxProvisioningType
JnxProvisioningType.description: There several choices for provisioning, these are the types: radius - provisioning via a radius server. local - local provisioning. ldap - provisioning via a LDAP server. securid- provisioning via RSA's SecurID provisioning server jsrc - provisioning via jsrc

jnxUserAAAStatTable.name: jnxUserAAAStatTable
jnxUserAAAStatTable.description: This table exposes the user authentication statistics.

jnxUserAAAStatAuthType.name: jnxUserAAAStatAuthType
jnxUserAAAStatAuthType.description: The entry indicates the authentication type. It uniquely identifies the statistics counters related to its authentication.

jnxUserAAAStatAccessAccepted.name: jnxUserAAAStatAccessAccepted
jnxUserAAAStatAccessAccepted.description: The number of access granted. It is an aggregated statistics for this type of authenticaiton.

jnxUserAAAStatAccessRejected.name: jnxUserAAAStatAccessRejected
jnxUserAAAStatAccessRejected.description: This number of access request rejected. It is an aggregated statistics for this type of authentication.

jnxUserAAAServerName.name: jnxUserAAAServerName
jnxUserAAAServerName.description: The server name which identifies the authentication server.

jnxUserAAAAddressPoolName.name: jnxUserAAAAddressPoolName
jnxUserAAAAddressPoolName.description: The address pool name which identifies the local address pool.

jnxAccessAuthServiceUp.name: jnxAccessAuthServiceUp
jnxAccessAuthServiceUp.description: An access authentication trap signifies that the specified service has started.

jnxAccessAuthServiceDown.name: jnxAccessAuthServiceDown
jnxAccessAuthServiceDown.description: An access authentication trap signifies that the specified service has been stopped.

jnxAccessAuthServerDisabled.name: jnxAccessAuthServerDisabled
jnxAccessAuthServerDisabled.description: An access authentication trap signifies that the External authentication server is not responding.

jnxAccessAuthServerEnabled.name: jnxAccessAuthServerEnabled
jnxAccessAuthServerEnabled.description: An access authentication trap signifies that the AAA client has changed the status of the External authentication server to UP.

jnxAccessAuthAddressPoolHighThreshold.name: jnxAccessAuthAddressPoolHighThreshold
jnxAccessAuthAddressPoolHighThreshold.description: An access authentication trap signifies that the address pool has reached its high threshold.

jnxAccessAuthAddressPoolAbateThreshold.name: jnxAccessAuthAddressPoolAbateThreshold
jnxAccessAuthAddressPoolAbateThreshold.description: An access authentication trap signifies that the address pool has reached its abate threshold

jnxAccessAuthAddressPoolOutOfAddresses.name: jnxAccessAuthAddressPoolOutOfAddresses
jnxAccessAuthAddressPoolOutOfAddresses.description: An access authentication trap signifies that an Out Of Addresses event occured on the pool.

jnxAccessAuthAddressPoolOutOfMemory.name: jnxAccessAuthAddressPoolOutOfMemory
jnxAccessAuthAddressPoolOutOfMemory.description: An access authentication trap signifies that an Out Of Memory event occured on the pool.

jnxUserAAAAccessPoolTable.name: jnxUserAAAAccessPoolTable
jnxUserAAAAccessPoolTable.description: The entries in this table specify the address pools.

jnxUserAAAAccessPoolEntry.name: jnxUserAAAAccessPoolEntry
jnxUserAAAAccessPoolEntry.description: A read-only description of the local address pools.

jnxUserAAAAccessPoolRoutingInstance.name: jnxUserAAAAccessPoolRoutingInstance
jnxUserAAAAccessPoolRoutingInstance.description: The routing instance of the address pool.

jnxUserAAAAccessPoolFamilyType.name: jnxUserAAAAccessPoolFamilyType
jnxUserAAAAccessPoolFamilyType.description: The family type of this pool.

jnxUserAAAAccessPoolInetNetwork.name: jnxUserAAAAccessPoolInetNetwork
jnxUserAAAAccessPoolInetNetwork.description: The Match criteria for this pool. Network or Prefix

jnxUserAAAAccessPoolInetPrefixLength.name: jnxUserAAAAccessPoolInetPrefixLength
jnxUserAAAAccessPoolInetPrefixLength.description: The Prefix Length for an IPv6 pool

jnxUserAAAAccessPoolOutOfMemory.name: jnxUserAAAAccessPoolOutOfMemory
jnxUserAAAAccessPoolOutOfMemory.description: The Number of times this pool has flagged an Out of Memory condition.

jnxUserAAAAccessPoolOutOfAddresses.name: jnxUserAAAAccessPoolOutOfAddresses
jnxUserAAAAccessPoolOutOfAddresses.description: The Number of times this pool has flagged an Out of Address condition.

jnxUserAAAAccessPoolAddressTotal.name: jnxUserAAAAccessPoolAddressTotal
jnxUserAAAAccessPoolAddressTotal.description: The total number of Addresses or prefixes in this pool.

jnxUserAAAAccessPoolAddressesInUse.name: jnxUserAAAAccessPoolAddressesInUse
jnxUserAAAAccessPoolAddressesInUse.description: The total number of Addresses or prefixes given out from this pool.

jnxUserAAAAccessPoolAddressUsage.name: jnxUserAAAAccessPoolAddressUsage
jnxUserAAAAccessPoolAddressUsage.description: The percentage of addresses used in this pool or linked pool. If this pool is the head of a linked chain of pools, this number reflects the Usage for the whole chain. Conversely, if this pool it part of a linked chain of pools but not the head of the chain, the value will not be used.

jnxUserAAAAccessPoolAddressUsageHigh.name: jnxUserAAAAccessPoolAddressUsageHigh
jnxUserAAAAccessPoolAddressUsageHigh.description: The configured high percentage threshold of addresses used in this pool or linked pool. An SNMP trap is generated when this threshold is exceeded. This trap will only be generated for unlinked pools or pools that are the head of a linked chain of pools Conversely, if this pool it part of a linked chain of pools but not the head of the chain, then no traps will be generated.

jnxUserAAAAccessPoolAddressUsageAbate.name: jnxUserAAAAccessPoolAddressUsageAbate
jnxUserAAAAccessPoolAddressUsageAbate.description: The configured abate percentage threshold of addresses used in this pool or linked pool. An SNMP trap clear is generated when address use falls below this threshold percentage. This trap will only be generated for unlinked pools or pools that are the head of a linked chain of pools Conversely, if this pool it part of a linked chain of pools but not the head of the chain, then no traps will be generated.

jnxUserAAADomainDelimiters.name: jnxUserAAADomainDelimiters
jnxUserAAADomainDelimiters.description: The list of delimiters used to separate the user's name from the user's domain in the username field. The default is '@'.

jnxUserAAADomainParseDirection.name: jnxUserAAADomainParseDirection
jnxUserAAADomainParseDirection.description: The direction in which the user's name is parsed: either search for domain delimiter from left to right or right to left; first delimiter marks boundry. The default is right to left.

jnxUserAAADomainTable.name: jnxUserAAADomainTable
jnxUserAAADomainTable.description: The entries in this table specify the assignment of a remote access user to a logical system, based on the user's domain.

jnxUserAAADomainEntry.name: jnxUserAAADomainEntry
jnxUserAAADomainEntry.description: A specification of the logical system to which users on a specified domain should be assigned.

jnxUserAAADomainName.name: jnxUserAAADomainName
jnxUserAAADomainName.description: The domain name uniquely identifying this entry.

jnxUserAAADomainStripDomain.name: jnxUserAAADomainStripDomain
jnxUserAAADomainStripDomain.description: Enables/disables the domain name stripping feature, which causes the system to strip the domain name before sending the access-request to RADIUS for authentication.

jnxUserAAADomainLogicalSystem.name: jnxUserAAADomainLogicalSystem
jnxUserAAADomainLogicalSystem.description: The name of the logical system, which will be used by the AAA subsystem for this session. If not specified, will be mapped to default.

jnxUserAAADomainRoutingInstance.name: jnxUserAAADomainRoutingInstance
jnxUserAAADomainRoutingInstance.description: The name of the routing instance, which will be used by the AAA subsystem for this session. If not specified, will be mapped to default.

jnxUserAAADomainAddrPoolName.name: jnxUserAAADomainAddrPoolName
jnxUserAAADomainAddrPoolName.description: The configured the address-pool-name for the domain name.

jnxUserAAADomainDynamicPorfile.name: jnxUserAAADomainDynamicPorfile
jnxUserAAADomainDynamicPorfile.description: The configured dynamic-profile which will be used for this session upon succeeding validation.

jnxUserAAADomainTargetLogicalSystem.name: jnxUserAAADomainTargetLogicalSystem
jnxUserAAADomainTargetLogicalSystem.description: The configured target logical-system that this session will need to be mapped to. If not specified, will be mapped to default.

jnxUserAAADomainTargetRoutingInstance.name: jnxUserAAADomainTargetRoutingInstance
jnxUserAAADomainTargetRoutingInstance.description: The configured routing-instance that this session will need to be mapped to.

jnxUserAAADomainDynamicProfile.name: jnxUserAAADomainDynamicProfile
jnxUserAAADomainDynamicProfile.description: The configured dynamic-profile to be used for this session.

jnxUserAAADomainTunnelTable.name: jnxUserAAADomainTunnelTable

jnxUserAAADomainTunnelEntry.name: jnxUserAAADomainTunnelEntry
jnxUserAAADomainTunnelEntry.description: A specification of the tunnels associated with a domain.

jnxUserAAADomainTunnelName.name: jnxUserAAADomainTunnelName
jnxUserAAADomainTunnelName.description: The domain name associated with this entry.

jnxUserAAADomainTunnelDefId.name: jnxUserAAADomainTunnelDefId

jnxUserAAADomainTunnelPreference.name: jnxUserAAADomainTunnelPreference
jnxUserAAADomainTunnelPreference.description: The tunnel's preference value associated with this entry.

jnxUserAAADomainTunnelRemoteGwName.name: jnxUserAAADomainTunnelRemoteGwName
jnxUserAAADomainTunnelRemoteGwName.description: This name specifies the hostname expected from the peer (the LNS) when a tunnel is setup.

jnxUserAAADomainTunnelRemoteGwAddress.name: jnxUserAAADomainTunnelRemoteGwAddress
jnxUserAAADomainTunnelRemoteGwAddress.description: IP address of LNS tunnel endpoint

jnxUserAAADomainTunnelSourceGwName.description: This name specifies the hostname expected from the peer (the LNS) when a tunnel is setup.

jnxUserAAADomainTunnelSourceGwAddress.name: jnxUserAAADomainTunnelSourceGwAddress
jnxUserAAADomainTunnelSourceGwAddress.description: The source address of the tunnel (overrides the default address for this LS/RI.)

jnxUserAAADomainTunnelSecret.name: jnxUserAAADomainTunnelSecret
jnxUserAAADomainTunnelSecret.description: The tunnel password associated with this entry.

jnxUserAAADomainTunnelLogicalSystems.name: jnxUserAAADomainTunnelLogicalSystems
jnxUserAAADomainTunnelLogicalSystems.description: The logical systems associated with this entty.

jnxUserAAADomainTunnelRoutingInstance.name: jnxUserAAADomainTunnelRoutingInstance
jnxUserAAADomainTunnelRoutingInstance.description: The routing instance associated with this entty.

jnxUserAAADomainTunnelMedium.name: jnxUserAAADomainTunnelMedium
jnxUserAAADomainTunnelMedium.description: The tunnel medium associated with this entry. The medium dictates the format of the tunnel address.

jnxUserAAADomainTunnelType.name: jnxUserAAADomainTunnelType
jnxUserAAADomainTunnelType.description: The tunnel type associated with this entry.

jnxUserAAADomainTunnelId.name: jnxUserAAADomainTunnelId
jnxUserAAADomainTunnelId.description: The tunnel identifier associated with this entry.

jnxUserAAADomainTunnelMaxSessions.name: jnxUserAAADomainTunnelMaxSessions
jnxUserAAADomainTunnelMaxSessions.description: The maximum number of tunnel sessions allowed in this tunnel entry.

jnxUserAAADomainPadnTable.name: jnxUserAAADomainPadnTable
jnxUserAAADomainPadnTable.description: The entries in this table specify the PPPoE active discovery network (PADN) parameters associated with a domain.

jnxUserAAADomainPadnEntry.name: jnxUserAAADomainPadnEntry
jnxUserAAADomainPadnEntry.description: A specification of the PPPoE active discovery network parameters associated with a domain.

jnxUserAAADomainPadnIpAddress.name: jnxUserAAADomainPadnIpAddress
jnxUserAAADomainPadnIpAddress.description: The IP address of this entry.

jnxUserAAADomainPadnIpMask.name: jnxUserAAADomainPadnIpMask
jnxUserAAADomainPadnIpMask.description: The IP mask of this entry.

jnxUserAAADomainPadnDistance.name: jnxUserAAADomainPadnDistance
jnxUserAAADomainPadnDistance.description: The administrative distance metric of this entry.

jnxUserAAAAccessProfileTable.name: jnxUserAAAAccessProfileTable
jnxUserAAAAccessProfileTable.description: The entries in this table specify the assignment of authentication methods for a particular subscriber type.

jnxUserAAAAccessProfileEntry.name: jnxUserAAAAccessProfileEntry
jnxUserAAAAccessProfileEntry.description: A specification of the authentication methods for a particular subscriber type.

jnxUserAAAAccessProfileAuthenticationOrd.name: jnxUserAAAAccessProfileAuthenticationOrder
jnxUserAAAAccessProfileAuthenticationOrd.description: The set of authentication mechanisms configured on this system. Each octet in this object contains one of the values defined in the JnxAuthenticateType TEXTUAL-CONVENTION. The system will sequence through each octet of this object starting at octet 1 and attempt to use the corresponding authentication protocol defined by JnxAuthenticateType. If an authentication protocol is configured and attempts to reach the authentication server fail, the system will move to the next octet in this object and retry the authentication in the form dictated by the corresponding authentication protocoltype. The process of sequencing thru each octet will stop if the authentication server is successfully contacted, or there are no more configured octets in this object.

jnxUserAAAAccessProfileAccountingOrder.name: jnxUserAAAAccessProfileAccountingOrder
jnxUserAAAAccessProfileAccountingOrder.description: The set of accounting mechanisms configured on this system. Each octet in this object contains one of the values defined in the JnxAccountingType TEXTUAL-CONVENTION. The system will sequence through each octet of this object starting at octet 1 and attempt to use the corresponding accounting protocol defined by JnxAccountingType. If an accounting protocol is configured and attempts to reach the accounting server fail, the system will move to the next octet in this object and retry the accounting in the form dictated by the corresponding accounting protocoltype. The process of sequencing thru each octet will stop if the accounting server is successfully contacted, or there are no more configured octets in this object.

jnxUserAAAAccessProfileAuthorizationOrde.name: jnxUserAAAAccessProfileAuthorizationOrder
jnxUserAAAAccessProfileAuthorizationOrde.description: The set of accounting mechanisms configured on this system. Each octet in this object contains one of the values defined in the JnxAuthorizationType TEXTUAL-CONVENTION. The system will sequence through each octet of this object starting at octet 1 and attempt to use the corresponding accounting protocol defined by JnxAuthorizationType. If an accounting protocol is configured and attempts to reach the accounting server fail, the system will move to the next octet in this object and retry the accounting in the form dictated by the corresponding accounting protocoltype. The process of sequencing thru each octet will stop if the accounting server is successfully contacted, or there are no more configured octets in this object.

Each octet in this object contains one of the values defined in the JnxProvisioningType TEXTUAL-CONVENTION. If an accounting protocol is configured and attempts to reach the accounting server fail, the system will move to the next octet in this object and retry the accounting in the form dictated by the corresponding accounting protocoltype. The process of sequencing thru each octet will stop if the accounting server is successfully contacted, or there are no more configured octets in this object.

jnxUserAAAAccessProfileAccStopOnFailure.name: jnxUserAAAAccessProfileAccStopOnFailure
jnxUserAAAAccessProfileAccStopOnFailure.description: Enables/disables the Acct-Stop message if a user fails authentication, but AAA-server grants access.

jnxUserAAAAccessProfileAccStopOnDeny.name: jnxUserAAAAccessProfileAccStopOnDeny
jnxUserAAAAccessProfileAccStopOnDeny.description: Enables/disables the Acct-Stop message if AAA-server denies access.

jnxUserAAAAccessProfileImmediateUpdate.name: jnxUserAAAAccessProfileImmediateUpdate
jnxUserAAAAccessProfileImmediateUpdate.description: Enables/disables the Acct-Update message on receipt of a Acct-response for the Acct-Start message.

jnxUserAAAAccessProfileCoaImmediateUpdat.name: jnxUserAAAAccessProfileCoaImmediateUpdate
jnxUserAAAAccessProfileCoaImmediateUpdat.description: Enables/disables the Acct-Update message on completion of processing a change of authorization.

jnxUserAAAAccessProfileInterval.name: jnxUserAAAAccessProfileInterval
jnxUserAAAAccessProfileInterval.description: The interval in minutes between accounting updates(Interim-stats off, if not specified).

jnxUserAAAAccessProfileStatType.name: jnxUserAAAAccessProfileStatType
jnxUserAAAAccessProfileStatType.description: The type of statistics are collected. These are the configured types: time - the option to report only uptime volume-time - the option to report both volume and uptime
